I"t<p>In this article, I will explain how you can use Trifacta to greatly simplify your data preparation efforts on data that is stored on premises. This follows a <code class="highlighter-rouge">hybrid cloud</code> model, where you freely mingle on-premises data stored in local disk drives and shared network filesystems, with data stored in the cloud in object storage, relational databases and cloud data warehouses.</p>

<h4 id="hybrid-cloud">Hybrid Cloud</h4>

<p>In recent years, we have seen cloud computing take off in a big way. Organizations are increasingly taking advantage of the elastic nature of the cloud, which allows them to achieve better utilization of compute resources. Rather than over-provisioning resources to accommodate peak capacity, you can adopt a strategy of <em>bursting to the cloud</em> to handle spikes in your infrastructure needs.</p>

